      Financial literacy
   =20
 =20
I have to say I=E2=80=99m excited for  New York=E2=80=99s new mayor:New Yor=
k Mayor-elect Eric Adams said schools should teach about cryptocurrency and=
 its technology, as he vows to build a crypto-friendly city when he takes o=
ffice in January.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CWhen I talked about blockchain and Bitcoins=
, young people on street stopped and asked me, =E2=80=98What is that?=E2=80=
=99=E2=80=9D Adams said on CNN=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CState of the Union=E2=80=
=9D on Sunday. Asked if he could explain Bitcoin, he laughed, saying that=
=E2=80=99s a challenge even for experts.=C2=A0Bitcoin means a =E2=80=9Cnew =
way of paying for goods and services throughout the entire globe,=E2=80=9D =
he said. =E2=80=9CAnd that=E2=80=99s what we must do - open our schools to =
teach the technology and teach this new way of thinking.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0We t=
alked a few weeks ago about =E2=80=9Cthe financial literacy industrial comp=
lex,=E2=80=9D in which big financial services firms partner with schools to=
 teach =E2=80=9Cfinancial literacy=E2=80=9D in ways that push their product=
s. I wrote:The purest possible mechanism of =E2=80=9Cfinancial literacy=E2=
=80=9D is (1) a banker comes to your school, (2) the banker tells you that =
to have a good life you need to start depositing money in the bank, (3) you=
r teacher nods approvingly, (4) you believe them and deposit money in the b=
ank and (5) the bank steals it.That sounds like a joke but it apparently ha=
s actually happened at least once! At an actual=C2=A0bank! (The trick is ad=
ding monthly maintenance fees for low-balance accounts, like the kind opene=
d by kids at their school.)Now: Think about crypto financial literacy! Scho=
ols are gonna invite random crypto firms in to teach =E2=80=9CWhat You Need=
 to Know About the Blockchain,=E2=80=9D and the crypto firms are going to c=
ome in and help kids set up crypto wallets and convert=C2=A0their lunch mon=
ey into Dogecoin, and then the crypto firms are going to steal absolutely a=
ll of the lunch money. And that will be a good educational experience! New =
York City kids will grow up knowing a lot more about crypto than kids elsew=
here! =E2=80=9CCrypto is a way for people to bamboozle me with technical-so=
unding terms and vague rhetoric about empowerment,=C2=A0and then steal my m=
oney,=E2=80=9D they will think! Correctly!
