 financial literacy industrial complex,=E2=80=9D in which big financial ser=
vices firms partner with schools to teach =E2=80=9Cfinancial literacy=E2=80=
=9D in ways that push their products. I wrote:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">The purest possible mechanism of =E2=80=9Cfinancial literac=
y=E2=80=9D is (1) a banker comes to your school, (2) the banker tells you t=
hat to have a good life you need to start depositing money in the bank, (3)=
 your teacher nods approvingly, (4) you believe them and deposit money in t=
he bank and (5) the bank steals it.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">That sounds like a joke but it apparently has actually happened at le=
ast once! At an actual=C2=A0bank! (The trick is adding monthly maintenance =
fees for low-balance accounts, like the kind opened by kids at their school=
.)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now: Think about crypto financial litera=
cy! Schools are gonna invite random crypto firms in to teach =E2=80=9CWhat =
You Need to Know About the Blockchain,=E2=80=9D and the crypto firms are go=
